<br>
Lodizal spawns at the gnoll camp in Iceclad(the one at the end of the ice bridge on your way to ToFS). He's a rare spawn though. When he does spawn he eats all the gnolls in the camp and moves down the beach alittle towards the 2nd ice bridge. <br>
<br>
BE WARNED!!!!! He hit for 300 and quad hits. He is also high MR so enc's and alot of healers and tanks are needed.<br>
<br>
On my server there's always someone parked at the gnoll camp waiting for Lodizal to spawn. Wehn he does the gnoll go nuts. <br>
<br>
GL getting him <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unosforatunytewind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nosforatu Nytewind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/4/01 12:52:58 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.toysnjoys.com/crap/doom.gif width=125></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lodizal</span><hr size=1> Maybe it has been awhile since you've met Lodizal, but he doesn't "eat all the gnolls".  The gnolls start to move around a lot, but they no longer engage him as they used to. <br>
<br>
